caption-thin.description: Extra small text size, typically used for fine print or disclaimers where the information is less critical but still necessary. In user interfaces, text-xs can be applied to subtle elements like tooltips or metadata, ensuring primary content remains the focal point. Despite its smaller size, attention to contrast and legibility is important, especially against complex backgrounds or in low-light environments.
